Whisk together soy sauce, 4 tablespoons CRISCO(R) Oil, honey, mustard and red pepper flakes, in a medium bowl. Add steak and toss. Marinate, covered at room temperature for 15 minutes. Heat 2 tablespoons CRISCO(R) Oil over moderately high heat, in a wok or heavy skillet. Heat until hot, but not smoking. Saute garlic, ginger, onion, bell peppers and broccoli, stirring, 5-7 minutes. Transfer mixture to another bowl. Heat 2 tablespoons CRISCO(R) Oil in wok over high heat until hot, but not smoking. Saute steak, stirring about 2 minutes. Stir in sauteed vegetables, water chestnuts and sesame seeds until heated through. Serve over steamed rice with additional soy sauce.